So, just to summarize, 

- if OOG occurs in pre-execution, **before entering the first frame**, revert state changes, refill the state costs with LIFO, burn any leftover regular with reservoir preserved;

- if OOG occurs **after entering the first frame**, keep the state changes made in pre-execution (auths), refill the state cost with LIFO (such as pre-charged account-creation cost), burn any leftover regular with reservoir preserved;

The reservoir portion will be preserved once it's initialized conceptually, in the pre-execution step. EIP-2780 needs to be edited

